    <note type="biography">
        <p>Diplomat and politician. Worked for the Foreign Office from 1846, and arranged for the transfer of the Ionian Islands to Greece in 1864. Conservative MP for Christchurch, 1874–80; Portsmouth, 1880–5. High commissioner in Egypt, 1885–7. Ambassador in Madrid, 1892–1900. Knighted, 1862.</p></note>
